: 日本人墓地公園位於[[後港_(新加坡)|後港]]泉和道，由妓院老闆二木多賀治郎於1891年捐出爲南洋姐的埋葬所。<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:シンガポール 戦跡記念碑めぐり|url=http://www.eva.hi-ho.ne.jp/yasu-ito/travel/ww2_singapore/ww2_singapore_body.shtml#Jpn_cemet|publisher=YASU|year=1999|language=ja|access-date=2014-11-28|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303120609/http://www.eva.hi-ho.ne.jp/yasu-ito/travel/ww2_singapore/ww2_singapore_body.shtml#Jpn_cemet|dead-url=no}}</ref> 墓地於1987年由新加坡政府憲報成爲紀念公園，佔地29,359平方公尺，共有910座墓碑，是東南亞佔地面積最大的日本人墓地。<ref>{{cite web|author=Lee Kip Lin|title=Japanese Cemetery Park : general view <nowiki>[1]</nowiki>|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/pictures/Details/49c4d5af-efeb-46d4-b21f-84a4ae9ff0df|publisher=National Library Board, Singapore|year=2009|quote=This 1993 photograph shows the Japanese Cemetery Park, located at Chuan Hoe Avenue. Gazetted as a memorial park in 1987, it is the largest Japanese cemetery in Southeast Asia.|language=en|access-date=2014-11-28|archive-date=2019-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031174419/http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/pictures/Details/49c4d5af-efeb-46d4-b21f-84a4ae9ff0df|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:シンガポール日本人墓地・戦争記念碑を訪ねて|url=http://www.geocities.jp/gogo_kyoro_chan_17/volume_01/229_singapore_war_memorial/index-japanese.html|publisher={{lang|ja|Go!Go!キョロちゃん!!!}}|language=ja|access-date=2014-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205071549/http://www.geocities.jp/gogo_kyoro_chan_17/volume_01/229_singapore_war_memorial/index-japanese.html|archive-date=2014-12-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

